  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nERC721Consecutive : next id is pain in this scenario. why not use something like snippet in below:\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction consecutiveTransfer(\r\n        uint256 fromTokenId,\r\n        uint256 toTokenId,\r\n        address fromAddress,\r\n        address toAddress\r\n    ) public {\r\n        require(fromTokenId <= toTokenId, \"Invalid token range\");\r\n\r\n        _consecutiveTransfer(fromTokenId, toTokenId, fromAddress, toAddress);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function _consecutiveTransfer(\r\n        uint256 currentTokenId,\r\n        uint256 toTokenId,\r\n        address fromAddress,\r\n        address toAddress\r\n    ) private {\r\n        emit ConsecutiveTransfer(currentTokenId, currentTokenId, fromAddress, toAddress);\r\n\r\n        if (currentTokenId < toTokenId) {\r\n            _consecutiveTransfer(currentTokenId + 1, toTokenId, fromAddress, toAddress);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n**openzeppelin v5 make Althing's better to use, but some codes make pain! \r\nthanks for response from community**\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n[ERC721Consecutive](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/7de6fd4a2604764497990bcc0013f95763713190/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721Consecutive.sol#L104) - [next id](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/7de6fd4a2604764497990bcc0013f95763713190/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721Consecutive.sol#L172)\r\n\r\n_snippet in above is experimental, i write that just for specific purposes..._",
